p:metadata.p:property: Validators locally re-execute blocks to ensure that the proposed state change is valid. They match their computed state_root with the proposed block's state_root. They also check the block information, such as the parent_root. If the proposed block has a different parent block than the validator believes it should have, they run the fork choice algorithm. Finally, they attest the block they believe is valid.
